Complete the Highwatch Castle Jumping Puzzle.

Complete the Lowtide Seagate Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Lowtide Ship Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Reverie Lobby Jumping Puzzle.

Complete the Sierhaven Flag Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Sierhaven Royal Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Sierhaven Tree Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Western Tower Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Verdant Lobby Jumping Puzzle.
Complete every Jumping Puzzle in the Celsian Isles.
Complete the Alnera Teleporter Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Darkest Depths Lobby Jumping Puzzle.
Complete The Fallen Forum Lobby Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Frostgate Cathedral Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Floating Carnival Jumping Puzzle.
You conquered the hardest parkour in the game - the Gardens of Yesel!
Complete the Mistport Lighthouse Jumping Puzzle.
Complete The Black Mist Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Sealed Remorse Lobby Jumping Puzzle.
Complete The Steelmeld Laboratory Jumping Puzzle.
Complete the Wispervale Academy Jumping Puzzle.

The master of the arena has fallen, but Yeigar swears to return...
Welcome, challengers and spectators alike, to the Arena of Terth!
Defeat Kaul, Soul of the Jungle.
Have 15 or more people spectating during any point of the fight.
Defeat Kaul in a match with 1 other player.
Defeat 100 or more spiders between all players during a Kaul fight.
You are a true master of the jungle.
Take part in a raid of 5 or more people where only you survive to defeat Kaul.
Take part in a raid of 10 or more people in which all party members die.
Defeat Kaul while having worn a Fedora for the entire duration of the fight.
Take part in a raid of 20 or more people, and be one of the winning players.
Take part in a raid of 10 or more people that suffers no casualties throughout the duration of the fight.
Die to Kaul when his health is at 10% or less.
Defeat Kaul with a team of exactly 3 clerics.
Get sent to judgement both times in a group of 10 or more, and succeed in both.
Defeat Kaul without having any class selected.
You discovered the Rush of Dissonance lobby.
Purchase the Remnant of the Rose.
Defeat 25 waves inside Rush of Dissonance.
Defeat 40 waves inside Rush of Dissonance.
Defeat 75 waves inside Rush of Dissonance.
C'Shura awaits you in the former resting place of Kaul. How will she greet you after so many years of isolation?
You have conquered the corrupted grounds of the Forsworn Sanctum.
You have awoken Ami Udake within the Forsworn Sanctum.
You've somehow beaten Winter Incarnate, most impressive.
Defeated Kaul alone under the Boots of Pride challenge.
Defeated Azacor alone on Hard mode under the Helm of Darkness challenge.
Defeated the Headless Horseman alone under the Leggings of Wrath challenge.
You have discovered the Verdant lobby. Something dark lies beyond...
You have conquered the threadwarped Remnants of Verdant.
You conquered a dungeon with all possible delve modifiers active!
Defeat Eldrask without having any class selected for the entire duration of the fight.
Defeat Eldrask with a raid of 10 or more players where no one dies.
Hit Eldrask with 10 or more icicles in a single fight.
Be the only survivor in a raid of 5 or more people.
Now you too shall outlast the others.
Use Annilys to survive a would-be fatal Titanic Rupture.
Survive Eldrask's Shatter attack during his final phase and win.
Defeat Eldrask with a team of exactly 3 warriors.
Defeat Eldrask, the last of the Frost Giants.
You have heard the song, and know its tale.
Get cursed by Hekawt 3 times in a single fight and win.
Survive Dies Irae at 5 Crystals or higher and win to tell the tale.
Enter Hekawt's Shadow Realm and escape with less than 1 second remaining.
Reports of my death were greatly exaggerated.
Slay a Player... as a revenant.
Defeat Hekawt with 10 or more players where no one dies.
Slay 3 Player Revenants outside the Shadow Realm in a single fight.
Defeat Hekawt with a team of exactly 3 Warlocks.
To conquer that who has conquered death...
Acquired a long lost Golden Key from Varcosa's ship, and slew the Mimic Queen guarding his final hoard.
Once again infused the Chime with the dying breath of Captain Varcosa, awakening its true potential.
You have discovered the Black Mist lobby. The crew is expecting you...
Cleared the Black Mist and conquered its captain, Varcosa.
Cleared the Black Mist with only 1 secret wall found.
Cleared the Black Mist with 4 people.
Found all hidden walls and every chest.
You have completed everything there is to do in the Parting Veil expansion and learned of dangers from Hekawt's shade.
You've found all the Rooster Caches!
You recovered the cache in Molta.
You recovered the cache in Steelmeld.
You recovered the cache in Rahkeri.
You recovered the cache in Nightroost.
You recovered the cache in Frostgate.
You recovered the cache in Alnera.
You recovered the cache in Wispervale.
You recovered the cache in Mistport.
You have discovered the Sealed Remorse lobby. What awaits you below...
You have conquered the depths of Sealed Remorse.
You conquered Sealed Remorse with over 200 seconds remaining on the clock!
You have parted the void and witnessed the Eternal Vigil.
Claim a Treasures of Viridia cache for your own.
Complete the special challenges of each region.
You fought off an ancient horror and claimed the Cyan Wool.
Deep below the ground lies an abandoned mineshaft, stained with secrets long forgotten. For what is a greater folly of man than the sin of greed?
In an attempt to uncover the secrets of Molta's past, you unintentionally opened a path to the surface for an evil that had been sealed away.
You fought back against Faimynyw's excursion into our world, and claimed powerful treasures.
Far, far below the waves lies a disturbance, a tear into our world. What possibly could have caused this?
You delved into the ruined Congress and found the truth about what occurred there.
Having passed through the time itself in the ruins of the Congress, the Fallen Forum awaits.
You found what the Teal Spirit was up to in the Ruins of the Congress, destroying a false wool to help free itself years ago. You destroyed the freed spirit, but Teal is still on the run.
You have scoured every corner of the Fallen Forum and collected yourself a Replica Olive Wool
You are a true master of the lore. Fred would be proud.

description.text: You explored the shifting depths of Steelmeld's undercity.
Deep below Steelmeld, sealed away by its unknown former inhabitants, lies secrets long since forgotten.
You assisted Fred on his journey to unlock a strange passage way leading deep below Steelmeld.
You assisted Fred with more research and ended up disturbing the city even further, bringing forth more dangerous rooms.
You discovered the true treasure within the Valley of Forgotten Pharaohs.
You excavated the lost city of Al Malakut and claimed the Gray Wool.
What would force a kingdom to lock off their capital? Al Malakut awaits its rediscovery.
You discoved the tomb of Tehkma Ka and found the lost city of Al Malakut.
You removed the explosives, defeated the bandits, and came away a stronger warrior.
Ahead lies the Alchemy Labs, bandits, and their cache of explosives.
You volunteered to take on bandits threatening to destroy the capital's Alchemy Labs.
Neither the Mages above nor the Alchemists below held power over you, as you claimed the Light Blue Wool.
There must be secrets hiding within this ancient place.
In your continued search for Ignos, you stumbled upon a secret of the Axtans that was best lost to time.
You ventured deep inside the Palace of Mirrors and saw what no others could: the Light Gray Wool.
Hidden within a citadel; hidden within a mirror. Alutana's palace stands strong.
Resolving the battle of light and darkness, now only their eclipse stands in your way.
You ventured through the lost empire of Viridia and claimed the Lime Wool.
Before you stands an empire lost to time, independent of Ishnir and Chillwind. What secrets from the distant past lie within?
You had an unexpected run-in with Xeno and discoved the lost empire of Viridia.
You found what the ancient temple was defending - the Magenta Wool.
From the depths, you can feel a sickness pouring. What lies below?
You restored the power of the Grand Maw and found a way inside a dungeon.
You claimed the Orange Wool, overcoming the experimented beastmen within the Menagerie.
You discovered a lost outpost of the Tlaxans, hiding more than just loot...
You made your way through C'Zanil's crypt and found a way inside a dungeon.
You journeyed through a twisted world of demons and claimed the Pink Wool.
Seasons bend and twist rapidly here. Deep in this dungeon lies a dark secret, do you dare seek it out?
You attuned yourself to the four seasonal shrines and discovered the Harmonic Arboretum.
You created Rootstrike, the sword of nobles.
Below Corsair's Claw, you learned the truth about the final voyage of the Pirate King Varcosa.
Below the mythical island of Corsair's Claw, the legendary pirate Varcosa awaits you.
Seeking out the final fate of Salazar the Great, you discovered the mythical island of Corsair's Claw.
The Willows, once guarded by a mysterious barrier, now lie defeated before you.
A lost grove stretches before you, filled with riches.
Following a note, you took a staff to four shrines and found a new dungeon.
Following a new trail, you took the elemental staff to four amplified shrines and found a Delve.
You defeated Kaul, saved the Narsens, and left victorious.
One man's dream is the Narsens' nightmare.
With the help of former Shaman Nai, you re-entered the dream and learned more about the nature of the Genius Loci- and angered Kaul yet again.
You discovered one of the many treasures of the Ephemeral Corridors, and many more remain hidden in its depths.
You discovered yet another of the many treasures of the Ephemeral Corridors, but could more remain hidden in its depths still?
You discovered another one of the many treasures of the Ephemeral Corridors, but still more remain hidden in its depths.
You find a maze of twisty little passages, all alike.
What started as a silly request for chores soon led you down a path to the Forsworn Sanctum.
After defying the laws of time itself, you witnessed a Wool disappear from this world.

description.text: Having passed through the Sacrarium of Aeons, a strange place lost to time now sits before you.
After traveling through the lost empire of Isharist, the man you traveled with, Max, held a dark secret.
You collected all Time Crystals without falling into the void once. Wonderful job!
You defeated the guardians of Quetzalcoatl, claiming the White Wool.
Before you lies the ancient sacrificial temple to a lost god...
You broke a powerful curse over the Blackroot Battlefield and found a way inside a dungeon.
The seasons overcome, now Kaul's power is released, but the Yellow Wool is now yours.
The seasons rage before you, a curse on the Sons of the Forest. Can you overcome them?
You reclaimed the ancient relic from the Sons of the Forest and have given Highwatch an opportunity to attack Verdant Fortress.
Win the King's Warden in Rock's Little Casino.
Win the Frost Giant's Crown in Monarch's Cozy Casino.
Use the Celsian Isles Transmogrifier 20 times.
Use the Celsian Isles Transmogrifier 50 times.
Use the Celsian Isles Transmogrifier 100 times.
Use the Celsian Isles Transmogrifier 200 times.
Use the Celsian Isles Transmogrifier 500 times.
While equipped, you deal an additional (level * 10)% damage if either you or the enemy you are damaging is in water.
Allows secondary enchants (ex: Shielding, Reflexes, etc.) to all work with the defense type (Armor or Agility) you have the most of.
Upon attacking an enemy, you gain (level * 10)% speed for 3 seconds. Upon breaking a spawner with a pickaxe, you gain (level * 5)% speed for 6 seconds.

One of Monumenta's primary defensive stats, along with Armor.
Multiplies received damage taken by 0.96^Agility.
If Armor and Agility are mixed, damage is multiplied by 0.96^(Armor + Agility - 0.5 * Armor * Agility / (Armor + Agility))
Reduces amount of healing received by (level * 10)%.
Decreases the cooldown of all of your skills by 5% per level multiplicatively.
Allows you to mine blocks underwater as if you were on land.

extra.text: Your attacks damage all enemies 3 blocks in front of you, in a 0.6-block-wide line.

description.text: Mining a spawner outside of water grants you (level * 3.75)% speed for 4s. Mining a spawner underwater refreshes (level * 0.5) breath.

If Armor and Agility are mixed, damage is multiplied by 0.96^(Armor + Agility - 0.5 * Armor * Agility / (Armor + Agility))

Applies the effects of Resurrection and Void Tether upon death while holding this item. This removes the enchant from the item. If the item has the enchant by default, it will be restored after every weekly update.
Mobs in a 2 block radius from you are slowed by (level * 2)% for 0.5 seconds. This is refreshed as long as they are in range.
Magically regrows the bark onto the logs you chop up.
When worn, an item with Curse of Binding cannot be removed unless it breaks or the player dies.
Applies Bleed (Enchantment level) for 5 seconds to all mobs struck by the Bleeding weapon. Bleed is a custom effect that applies (level * 10)% Slowness and Weakness to mobs under 50% Max Health.
After being hit, gain (level * 1.25)% damage reduction for 5 seconds, refreshed on being hit.
Your weapon deals anywhere between +Level and -Level damage, in integer increments. This effect is halved for sweep attacks. This only works in your main hand.
Deal (level * 1)% additional damage to any mob that is on fire, slowed, or stunned.
Items reinforced with Colossal don't take durability damage 50% of the time. Works with the Unbreaking enchant.
Enchantments that function on consumable items.
Holding or equipping one item is fine, but too much corruption is bad for you...
Enchantments that grant a cosmetic effect to your items.
When struck in combat, you are slowed by 30%.
Curses that cause negative effects. Be careful!
Gives night vision when held or worn.
Strips the bark off the logs you chop down.
Applies a Decay effect that deals 1 damage every (40 / level) ticks for 4 seconds.
Enchantments that reduce the damage you take in some way or another.
From the Depths and the Delves, offering special enchantments that can be specially added to your gear!
Allows you to move faster by (level * 33)% when in water.
While equipped or stored in inventory, the player and mobs hit gain an aura of divine particles.

extra.text: You deal more damage to human-like enemies - illagers, vexes, witches, piglins, piglin brutes, golems and giants.

description.text: Increases the speed at which you break blocks with the enchanted item. If on an Axe, it also increases the chance of stunning a shield by an additional 5% per level.
When you gain XP, you have a 0.25% chance per XP point per level to repair all currently equipped items by 1% of their max durability. There is also a slight prioritization to more damaged items.
All good things must come to an end. Will vanish when you log out, transfer shards, drop it, or try to move them to another inventory.
Class abilities cooldowns are reduced by (level * 1)%.

Deal (level * 4) damage in a 5 block radius that can apply the effects of Decay, Fire, Ice, and Thunder Aspect to nearby mobs, and Adrenaline, Sapper to nearby players, when a spawner is broken with the item. Thunder Aspect applied via Eruption stuns 100% of the time and adds (level * 0.5) seconds of stun.
Gain (Level*20%) effective Agility on hits taken within 1.5 seconds of any previous hit.
Gain (Level*20%) effective Agility when taking damage from a source further than 5 blocks from the player.
After killing an enemy, you deal (level * 1.5)% extra damage for 4 seconds.
Deals 15 damage and applies Slowness III to mobs summoned within the Valley of Forgotten Pharaohs.
Damaging an enemy with an ability increases your movement speed by (level * 1)% for 5 seconds, stacking up to 3 times.
While equipped or stored in inventory, gain an aura of festive particles that improve with every additional item.
Ignites the target for (level * 4) seconds when dealing melee or projectile damage.
Multiplies fire damage by (0.96) ^ (2 * level). Reduces fire duration by 10% per level.
Increases the number of resources gained when breaking ores and certain other blocks that drop resources, based on level.

While your item is with you, you gain an aura of gold particles. While dropped, your item gains similar particles. Additional items increase your particles, capped at 10.
A reward for winning the voting raffle.
While equipped or held, gain Water Breathing.
Adds (level * 0.5) extra damage per debuff on the target.
While dropped, items with Hope are indestructable and take 15 minutes to despawn.
Applies (level * 10)% Slowness for 4 seconds when dealing melee or projectile damage. Deals 1 extra damage to Blazes.
Increases the cooldown of all of your skills by 5% per level multiplicatively.
Deals an extra 1 damage per level to enemies that are on fire, and 0.5 damage per level to enemies that are not on fire.
Your item gains infinite power. Bows never consume their arrow, crossbows return their loaded arrow, potions never go empty, and food never runs out.
Enchantments that can be specially added to your gear, should you pay the costs!
Right clicking a potion with this enchant will instantly apply its effects to the player using it.
Gain (Level*20%) effective Armor when taking the same type of mob damage consecutively (Melee, Projectile, Blast, or Magic).
Some items are too fragile to be repaired...
Fills the hunger bar when eaten. Heals 4 hearts and gives 20% resistance for 4 seconds. 25 second cooldown.
Adds (level * 3) blocks to your knockback on melee strikes.

extra.text: Your critical melee attacks heal you. Normal melee attacks also heal you, but for less.
Main hand, off hand, armor slots

description.text: Prevents the item from being swapped by a lockbox.
Increases common loot drops by (Enchantment level) chances.
Decreases the time spent waiting for a fish to appear by (level * 5) seconds.
A special item, used to craft another item - often Patron related ones. Items with this enchant also can be used as crafting materials in regular vanilla Minecraft recipes.
Items with Mending that are worn or held repair 2 durability per xp orb consumed, chosen at random among your items with Mending.
Mining a spawner debuffs all enemy types that spawner could spawn in a 4 block radius with (level * 3.75)% Weaken for 2 seconds.
Crossbows enchanted with Multishot fire 3 projectiles at once in a spread pattern. Only one projectile is consumed and only one out of the 3 can be picked up off the ground.
Allows a tool to change shape when you right-click with it. Level I lets it to cycle between a shovel and an axe. Level II additionally lets it cycle to being a pickaxe.
You move (level * 3)% faster when in water.
Enchantments that grant a passive effect when used or worn.
You will not drop this item on death.

Dying with an item infused with Phylactery saves (10% * level) of your experience points in your grave. This stacks additively with itself across all items equipped. Experience will only be saved if you died with more than 100 experience points. Additionally, keep potion effects upon dying for (10% * level) of the duration.
Arrows shot from a crossbow with Piercing can pass through up to the number of entities equal to the enchantment level.
Projectiles deal an additional (level * 2) damage if the enemy is within 8 blocks.
Gain (Level*20%) effective Armor when above 90% Max Health.
While held, grants 25% damage reduction in Celsian Isles areas, or 15% damage reduction in King's Valley areas.
When your melee attack kills an enemy, all nearby enemies in a 3-block cube take (level * 10)% of the damage dealt. Your weapon's Fire/Ice/Thunder Aspect, Decay and/or Bleed also get applied.
Decreases the time it takes to load a crossbow by (level * 0.25) seconds.
While held in your main hand, gain Glowing and Night Vision for 30s. You must be the soulbound owner of your item for this to work.
Restores 6 hunger and 6 saturation when eaten. Gives the player +15% to all damage and +15% speed for 15 seconds. 25 second cooldown.
Enchantments that grant special ranged effects.
When fired, your crossbow knocks you back a short distance, increasing with level. Crouching while firing prevents the recoil, but places crossbows on cooldown for 0.5 seconds.
1 second after taking magic or blast damage, deal (level * 6)% of the ability's damage to all mobs in a 4 block radius, bypassing I-frames.
Gain (Level*20%) effective Agility when there are 4 or more enemies within 8 blocks.
When equipped, regain 1 * sqrt(level) health every 3s overall, received in small increments 4 times per second.
While equipped, you deal an additional (level * 10)% damage to elite enemies and (level * 5)% damage to boss enemies.
Extends your breathing time underwater by (level * 15) seconds.
When you are about to die, this item provides Absorption and Regeneration, destroying itself in the process.
Arrows have a (level * 10)% chance to not be consumed.
A Trident with Riptide can only be thrown when in water. When this happens, you are launched with your Trident a distance based on your Riptide level.
Enchantments found while adventuring in Monumenta.
Restore (Enchantment Level) health by breaking a spawner.

Damage from attacks applied to the lower half of your max health is multiplied by 0.9^(level). Attacks received while under this threshold get their damage reduced; attacks that bring you under this threshold have the portion of the damage that is applied past the threshold reduced.
Gain Level*20% effective Armor when taking damage from an enemy within 2.5 blocks. Taking damage that would stun a shield and activates Shielding disables Shielding for 5 seconds.
When used to break a spawner, take (level) damage. This damages armor and bypasses damage reductions.
Allows blocks to drop as themselves instead of their normal drop, when broken with an item with this enchantment.

Deals (level * 2) damage to everything unaffected by Smite or Duelist; Spiders, Silverfish, Bees, Cave Spiders, Creepers, Ghasts, Shulkers, Endermen, Blazes, Slimes, Magma Cubes, Wolves, Ravagers, Hoglins, and passive animal mobs.
Adds (level * 2) extra damage to melee hits against Undead mobs.
Projectiles deal an additional (level * 2) damage if the enemy is further than 16 blocks.
When on soul sand or soul soil, your speed will increase by (level * 10.5)%.
Increases the damage of spells (+20% Spell Power increases the damage of all spells by 20%, for example), and only works with Mage skills. Spell Power stacks with the Magic Damage attribute.
Depletes your saturation and current hunger points by (Enchantment level) upon consuming the item cursed with Starvation. It fully depletes saturation, then moves on to removing hunger points.
While Stasis is active, you are immovable, immune to all damage and effects, and cannot use any interactions or abilities.

Designates that an item has had stat tracking added to it via a Patron. Stats are only tracked if used by the person who added it as long as they're still a patron. A variety of different stats can be tracked, such as Mobs Killed, Times Consumed, Boss Damage Dealt, and more! Consider becoming a patron if you aren't one already to gain access to this perk.
Scaling with percent health missing, gain up to (Level*20%) effective Armor. (0.25% armor speed per 1% health lost, up to 20% armor)
While your item is equipped, you gain an upper aura of black particles.
Increases amount of healing received by (level * 10)%.
Increases sweep damage by (1 + Attack Damage * (level / (level + 1))).
Gain (Level*20%) effective Agility on the first hit taken after 4 seconds of taking no damage. Half of the bonus is granted after 2 seconds of taking no damage.
Right-clicking consumes the item, instantly launching an arrow that deals 7-9 damage and applies the respective effects if the arrow is tipped.

Has a (level * 10)% chance to stun a mob for 2 seconds (0.5 for Elites) when dealing melee damage, or for 0.5 seconds (0 for Elites) when dealing projectile damage. Deals 1 extra damage to Guardians and Iron Golems.
Enchantments that grant a helpful effect to your tools and weapons.
Increases the amount of healing you do to others by (level * 5)%.

Some items simply cannot be used correctly if your hands are full... Reduces attack damage, attack speed, and spell power of the item, reduces player movement speed, and restricts the ability to throw/shoot projectiles if held while also having an offhand equipped. Two-handed swords count as holding two swords for sake of Rogue abilities.

Makes gear break (level + 1)x slower.
Works the same on tools, weapons, and armor.
All other Delve Infusions you are currently benefitting from gain (level * .25) levels of this Infusion.
Increases your Knockback Resistance by 0.4 per level.
Heal (level * 2.5)% of your max health whenever you slay an elite or boss enemy.
When held in inventory, an item with Curse of Vanishing shatters upon death. Curse of Vanishing II will cause the item to be completed deleted upon death.
If you die in the void, this item is consumed and a single block of obsidian is placed underneath you.
Enchantments that alter your attacks and increase the damage of them.
May be held in the offhand without incurring a debuff from the Two Handed curse.

title.text: A Study in Crimson Part One

description.text: The Crimson King called in your contract. You worked with him to dig through memories, searching for a way to restore the Crimson Wool.
Commanded by the Order of Glass to uncover Octavius's misdeeds, you failed when the evidence was taken by Duchess Emmeline.
Raiding two bandit camps, you learned the truth of Octavius's shady business dealings.
Stefan needed a pretzel recipe, and you stole it for him in exchange for some strange rewards.
A landslide ruined Blackjack Stan's smuggling den. Of course, he sent you into a deadly cave to retrieve a sword he needed.
Because of your actions, Oceangate Lighthouse burns brighter than ever before.
Working with Nurse Deidre, you made a cast for Melinda and repaired more than just a bone.
After defeating Virius, Nelfine's memory has truly returned and with it her friendship with Arian.
You went on a clucking silly adventure, and defeated the god of pigs.
You solved mysterious puzzles leading to Psychie's lost love, Cupid.
You helped Claude make his culinary masterpiece. After fighting him, his appetite for human flesh should be gone.
You helped a weird little man be slightly less weird and stop writing fanfiction about you.
You've completed a race around Sierhaven. Search towns around the world for more races.
You've purified the waters of the Fountain of Miracles, corrupted by dark magic from deep in the jungle.
You helped an old Tlaxan regain his musical talent, and got music of your own in return...
Choose your class proper and carry on with your adventure!
Following in the footsteps of Aurora, you discovered the truth behind her disappearance...
The lights have shown you the way in the darkness, where you found a strange letter...
A secret warehouse lies beneath Sierhaven, filled with missing people. Eowen has closure, but mysteries still remain.
Helping Archmage Vargos, you translated an ancient Tlaxan poem and learned the tragic history of the mage council.
You investigated the secrets of the Arena, instead discovering the Crimson King was involved the whole time.
You reunited Leonard and his adorable pet Mr. Snuggles.
Sergeant Sigrun needed your help finding her soldiers. Unfortunately, the Jaguar Tribes found them first.
You helped restore Nelfine's memory. Hopefully she'll remember more and more with time...
You saved the Axtan Monks from the Sons of the Forest, a shadowy cabal of druids.
What seemed like a mission to find a lost book turned into a search through the mysterious Grove, where you encountered the demon summoner Azacor.
Levyn is more of a pirate than ever after you found him a parrot and peg-leg.
Braving several lava-filled caverns, you brought Carbocius magma samples from around the valley.
Welcome to Monumenta, the CTM MMO RPG!
Highwatch is saved from a swarm of ghasts and blazes, and you've uncovered the true plans of the Sons of the Forest.
Discover the City of Sierhaven, capital of King's Valley
The hunt for the Snow Wool led you to its destruction, and you battled its spirit to save the holidays!
You stole a powerful binding spell from the Sons of the Forest, hindering their plans! No doubt they are planning their revenge...
You repaired another spyglass, this time for Mayleen's friend Montana. While secretive, it seems there's more here than just stargazing...
You repaired the telescope, but something more sinister is yet to unfold...
By breaking into an armory and spinning gears, you helped Mayleen fix her telescope.
After running around Sierhaven, you helped deliver a package of supplies to the small town of Nyr.
Overcoming another trip into Velara and an attack by the Sons of the Forest, you connected Ta'Eldim and Sierhaven.
When T'Xoc asked for your help to locate a missing Tlaxan Elder, you followed their trail back to the Verdant Fortress... What lurks inside?
Nyr was at risk of falling to a deadly plague, but you and C'Taz created an ancient medicine to save the town.
You caught a royal fish (with strange defenders) and won a fishing contest. Display the trophy proudly.
You helped Laura find her diary. With the information stored in the book, the northern path to Sierhaven may be a lot safer now!
By solving the mirror puzzles in Ta'Eldim's shrine, you gained the trust of Barras, the Shrinetender.
T'Lm told you of his people's hidden town, Ta'Eldim. While you have gained entry, not all the townspeople trust you yet...
You have earned the title of Dreamwalker by interacting with the dreamers.
You have continued your journey of Dreamwalker, into realms never before walked.
The Masked Man, an agent of Calder, has been stopped and the Black Shard reclaimed from the Sons of the Forest. They will no longer threaten the valley with their dark magic.
Dimitri's mentor, Ignos, has vanished, but you found closure and a clue in his cryptic journal.
You passed the Frostgate Target Test and learned the Ranger Specialization.
With the help of some researchers, you fought against the former Vizier of Al Malakut, Hekawt, now a lich, and prevented him from causing further destruction.
The Ishnir Trade may have suffered a catastrophic loss, but with your help they should be able to recover.
You learned from the Giant slayer himself and fought a Giant yourself, preventing total destruction of the Isles.
You've helped Riaz recover his lost supplies.
You helped Levyn with a deal to get information, but ended up getting tricked in the process.
You gather the pelts of rare creatures and learned the Hunter Specialization.
The Duchess used you to spy on diplomats. Will it be you that puts an end to her reign of terror?
You assisted in retrieving a hitlist from pirates and learned the Assassin Specialization.
You helped save Mistport's massive underground farm.
You assisted in disrupting a tower's magic and learned the Berserker Specialization.
You sought out a survivor of the Congress, but things didn't quite go as expected.
You investigated a brutal murder of a rich Countess! You caught the murderer! He's behind bars... for now.
You followed a mysterious and baffling trail that may have brought back a friend...
Safar was pleased with your work, The Ishnir Trade knows of your name now...
You fought illusions of the past and learned the Harbinger Specialization.
Following the path of a Lieutenant of the Black Mist, you discovered a Breach below the ocean where something evil approaches.
You may have destroyed the castle's floor and table, but the Marshall can get some rest.
You've helped Herriot realise a new destiny which is awaiting for him.
Whether you like it or not, Lincoln's pesky client has been dealt with.
Your first initial heist as a Night Rooster.
You helped Galablad protect Grethony and learned the Guardian Specialization.
You helped Ellen establish a communication network and learned the Hierophant Specialization.
Working with Izzy, Levyn, and clearly Not Samwell, you went on a piratey adventure and discovered something below the City of Bones.
You rooted out the Masked in Ishnir's government after getting unexpectedly arrested.
You helped Bero continue his experiments and learned the Reaper Specialization.
You've assisted Myra in conquering her fear.
You found your way through a very dark maze and learned the Tenebrist Specialization.
Complete all Specialization Trials in the Celsian Isles.
You helped out the Teacher in Mistport to reopen the Specialization School.
You helped create a barrier spell and learned the Arcanist Specialization.
Ebonee and her friends are now known among their peers for legendary pranks.
Retrieved by any means necessary, the book is now back in Saanavi's hands.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Teal Wool, and Selari's future plans.
You discovered the workshop of a mysterious man named Selari and learned more about the nature of the White Wool.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Orange and Magenta Wools.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Light Blue and Yellow Wools.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Crimson Wool and Selari himself.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Lime and Pink Wools.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Gray and Light Gray Wools.
You delved further into Selari's workshop and learned more about the nature of the Cyan and Purple Wools.
You slayed a Wither and learned the Paladin Specialization.
You've assisted Nitreia in fixing Steelmeld's agricultural problems.
You assisted Captain Lamis and ended up getting attacked by a strange assailant.
You rooted out the Masked in the Chillwind's government while trying to protect Wispervale from Mage Hunters.
The Fist of Turaal is operational once again now that you have helped Lt. Aulber.
You have completed the Professor's challenges... for now.
You have completed even more of the Professor's challenges... for science!
Now Miane's stable is full of life once more!
You retrieved Myriad's lost chestplate, but his luck remains missing...
You helped find a 'cure' for the queen of Frostgate and learned the Apothecary Specialization.
Following the ramblings of a drunken pirate, you discovered the ghost ship of Captain Varcosa - the Black Mist.
You searched out information about the truth of the war, and ended up siding with a nation.
You've proven yourself to the Night Roosters and joined their ranks.
You've found an ancient temple of the Viridian Empire and retrieved a cursed artifact.
You defeated Richter the Unyielding and learned the Swordsage Specialization.
Now with the Doctor's ingredients retrieved, you have gained access to his remedy in Mistport!
You assembled your pirate crew once again and embarked on a journey to the Celsian Isles.
You unlocked your subconscious through meditation and learned the Elementalist Specialization.
You investigated the death of Vargos' apprentice and found Xeno at the center of the incident.
You searched out clues for Xeno and discovered his connection with Calder.
